goals.rationale: This visualization will show the average number of commits made per day, allowing us to identify the busiest days and any trends over time.

goals.rationale: This visualization will show the correlation between the number of commits made and the day of the week, allowing us to identify any patterns or trends in the data.

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Count')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of commits made to Github repositories?')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Commits')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    data = data.groupby('day').mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='day', y='count', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average commits per day: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].mean()))
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Day')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average number of commits')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of commits made per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = data['time'].dt.day_name()
    data = data.groupby('day_of_week').mean().reset_index()
    sns.scatterplot(x='day_of_week', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of commits made and the day of the week?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Commits')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from datetime import datetime

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='hour', bins=24, color='blue', kde=False)
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Commits')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the time of day when commits were made?')
    plt.xticks(range(0, 24))
    plt.xlim(-0.5, 23.5)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
